# PostgreSQL migrations, scheduler, and SQL assets

## Policy
- **PostgreSQL only** for new migration and SQL work. Do not extend MySQL migration branches unless the user explicitly requests it (see `.cursor/rules/deprecated-mysql.mdc`).

## Main application migrations
- **Runner**: `src/db/migrate.ts` (invoked via `npm run db:migrate` and flags in root `README.md`).
- Typical phases (match user intent to the right flag):
  - `--schema-only` — `npm run db:migrate:schema`
  - `--procedures-only` — `npm run db:migrate:procedures`
  - `--cron-only` — `npm run db:migrate:cron`
  - `--seed-only` — `npm run db:migrate:seed`
  - `--fdw-only` — `npm run db:migrate:fdw`
- When editing migration behavior, keep **main project** and **`migration-kit`** in sync when the kit is meant to mirror production runs (`migration-kit/README.md` calls this out).

## Migration kit (standalone runner)
- **Purpose**: run DB migrations **without** deploying the full Next.js app on a server.
- **Location**: `migration-kit/`
- **Commands**: `npm run migrate`, `migrate:schema`, `migrate:procedures`, `migrate:cron`, `migrate:seed`, `migrate:fdw` (see `migration-kit/README.md`).
- If you change `src/db/migrate.ts` or shared SQL under `scripts/success_rate/`, verify whether **`migration-kit/src/db/migrate.ts`** and **`migration-kit/scripts/success_rate/*`** need the same change.

## Processing scheduler (technical reference)
- Per `docs/technical/processing-scheduler.md`:
  - **PostgreSQL** path may use **pg_cron**-based scheduling where available.
  - Some environments use an **app-level** scheduler option when DB scheduler tooling is not available.
  - **Procedure definitions** are sourced from **`scripts/success_rate`** (see that folder’s README).
- When touching scheduled processing, read `docs/technical/processing-scheduler.md` and `scripts/success_rate/README.md` before changing behavior.

## FDW
- Foreign Data Wrapper setup is a **dedicated migration phase** (`db:migrate:fdw` / `migrate:fdw`). Do not fold FDW into unrelated changes unless the task requires it.

## Agent rules
- Prefer **Postgres** artifacts (`*.postgres.sql`, Postgres branches in migrate logic) over MySQL.
- After SQL or migrate changes, mention which **npm script** the operator should run (full vs phase-only) when that matters for safety.
